ssion fragment** instead of the full interaction. The first turns of a session (before a branch/PR association is stable, or whenever the workspace read blips) are the most commonly lost.\n    34\t- This is **silent**: nothing reports that turns were dropped for lack of association (it's distinct from the bounded-projection truncation warnings, which were `false` here).\n    35\t- It makes the agent-trail product look broken (\"my messages aren't showing up\") when the capture+index layer is the cause.\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-26T11:36:16.749Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}